class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLastWord(String s) {
        char[] arr=s.toCharArray();
        int i=s.length()-1;
        int res=0;
        while(i>=0 && arr[i]==' '){
            i--;
        }
        while(i>=0 && arr[i]!=' '){
            res++;
            i--;
        }
        return res;
     }
}
Note:
the first loop searches for the extra spces at the end, id there is any extraspace it will reduce the size of the string,
then the second loops will count the length of the last word untill the spaces comes.
